Former Health Minister, Dr Zweli Mkhize. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - Former Health Minister Zweli Mkhize files a supplementary affidavit to have the Special Investigating Unit (SIU) report reviewed and set aside. Mkhize stands accused of allegedly putting pressure on Department officials to award a controversial R150 million tender to Digital Vibes, a company owned by his alleged associates and his family. In June last year, the SIU made adverse findings against Mkhize. In the latest court papers, he says the SIU approached this investigation with a predetermined outcome. READ: COVID-19 Corruption | SIU, Digital Vibes to go before tribunal He is seeking that the findings and recommendations be set aside and declared unlawful and unconstitutional. Mkhize is accusing the SIU of leaving out important evidence. He also claims the SIU ignored evidence that the former Health DG played a significant role in the awarding of the tender.